-- Mexico Stocks: Mexichem, Elektra, Comercial Chedraui Were Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-03-26T21:25:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/mexico-stocks-mexichem-elektra-comercial-chedraui-were-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC index rose 1.4 percent to 38,863.15, a record.  Mexichem SAB (MEXCHEM*)  , the chemical producer that has
bought more than 15 companies since 2007, gained 2.6 percent to
48.54 pesos.  Banco Santander SA (SAN)  said it expects the company to
“positively surprise” in the next two quarters and reiterated
its “buy” recommendation, according to an e-mailed research
note.  Retail companies were among the biggest gainers in Mexico
after U.S. Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  said that
accomodative monetary policy is still needed to spur jobs.  Grupo Elektra SAB (ELEKTRA*)  , the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , rose 4.6
percent to 1,176.63 pesos.  Grupo Comercial Chedraui SAB (CHDRAUIB) 
, the supermarket chain based in Xalapa, Mexico,
rose 2 percent to 33.61 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
